# Sync Agent Context

Regenerate all agent entrypoint files from the single source of truth in
`docs/agent-shared.md`.

## When to use

- After editing `docs/agent-shared.md`.
- After editing delta headers in `scripts/sync-agent-context.sh`.
- Before committing agent configuration changes.

## Steps

1. Run `scripts/sync-agent-context.sh`
2. Verify output: `git diff --stat` — expect changes in `CLAUDE.md`, `AGENTS.md`, `.cursorrules`
3. Spot-check shared core is identical across all three files
4. Stage: `git add CLAUDE.md AGENTS.md .cursorrules`

## Failure handling

- "Missing shared core" → ensure `docs/agent-shared.md` exists
- Divergent output → compare `docs/agent-shared.md` against "Shared Core" sections

## Scope

- Does NOT edit `docs/agent-shared.md` — make changes there first
- Does NOT sync `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` files
